item.name: Airline
item.description:
APIs to manage the airline resource.

This is the only resource available currently as a REST endpoint.
It means there are endpoints for every operation: create, delete, update, search.

Ideally, there should be also REST endpoints for other resources, such as Flights, Cities and Airports.

Auth
item.description:
Bearer Token authentication.

The authentication uses a bearer token to validate the requests.

That means, you can send a request to `/register` endpoint to create a user.
After that, login with the user sending a request to `/login` to receive the Bearer Token.

The Bearer token must be sent in the `Authorization` header in subsequent requests to endpoints that require authentication.

request.description: Authenticate user and returns a `bearer` token.
Invalidate the user's current access token.

query.description: Date of departure. Must be a valid date in the format Y-m-d.
Trip type, it can be a **one-way** or **round-trip**.
Date of the return trip. This field is required when type is round-trip.  Must be a valid date. Must be a valid date in the format Y-m-d. Must be a date after or equal to departure_date.
Number of stops, can be blank(all flights), 0(direct flights only) or 1. When 1, will filter flights with 1+ stops. Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 1.
IATA Code of the airline to filter the flights.
Size per page. Defaults to 10. Must not be greater than 100.
Sorting field, currently can be only **price**.
Sorting order, can be either **asc** or **desc**. This field is required when sort_by is present.

request.description:
Search for flights according to search criteria and return paginated result.

Briefly, flights can be searched by departure airport, arrival airport, departure date and return date(if is a round trip).
